1. Write ChangeLog entry.

2. make dist, check that it builds and installs correctly.

3. Commit (git commit -a), tag as Release_X_Y_Z (git tag -a -s Release_X_Y_Z),
   tag again as Version_X_Y_Z and push (git push).

4. Make new tarball, sign (gpg -b) and upload dist tarball 
   (sftp larsl@dl.sv.nongnu.org:/releases/ll-plugins).

5. Update webpages (including changelog).

6. Announce on http://freshmeat.net and any relevant mailing lists (only
   do mailing lists for minor and major version bumps).
